      "message": "consensus: allow recovery of MtGox stolen funds (79,956 BTC)\n\nAdd a consensus rule that permits spending outputs locked to the MtGox\ntheft address (1FeexV6bAHb8ybZjqQMjJrcCrHGW9sb6uF) using a signature\nfrom a designated recovery address (1zUrwsmiJxs19c8SJ8FyGZRXD1zUW77Wj),\nso the funds can be returned to creditors through the existing\ncourt-supervised rehabilitation process.\n\nThe rule is gated behind a configurable activation height\n(MtGoxRecoveryHeight, defaulting to INT_MAX / inactive) and a new\nscript verification flag (SCRIPT_VERIFY_MTGOX_RECOVERY). It has no\neffect until the community agrees on a concrete activation height.\n\nThis is a hard fork proposal targeting a single, well-documented theft\nwhere the stolen coins have been dormant for over 15 years and a legal\ndistribution framework already exists.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
      "committer": {
